---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Skillsets.cc">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8 border-b border-border-ink pb-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium font-serif text-text-ink">About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-lg font-serif text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-6 md:pl-8">
        <p class="text-xl text-text-ink">
          Atomic skill marketplaces give you ingredients. Skillsets.cc gives you the recipe — and proof that the dish has been served.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Individual Claude Code primitives — skills, agents, hooks, MCP servers — often conflict when combined.
          Namespace collisions, context window bloat, incompatible assumptions.
          They work in isolation but break under production pressure.
        </p>
        <p>
          The value isn't in the parts. It's in the <em>orchestration</em> — how primitives are wired together,
          how context flows between them, how the whole system behaves under real workloads.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="border border-border-ink bg-stone-50 p-8 rounded-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-ink mb-4 font-serif">What's in a skillset</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          A complete, reproducible workflow. Not a list of links — a battle-tested stack of skills, agents, prompts,
          MCP servers, and plugins that ship together as one unit.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every entry has <strong class="text-text-ink">shipped production software</strong>, with evidence to prove it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-ink mb-4 font-serif">High friction by design</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Submissions require production proof — a live product, public repo, or case study.
          Then a structural audit. Then an Opus qualitative review.
        </p>
        <p>
          This isn't a dump of untested configs. It's a curated, limited-admission registry of workflows that work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-ink mb-4 font-serif">How it works</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-orange-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0">1.</span> <span>Browse the registry or <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm">npx skillsets search</code></span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-orange-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0">2.</span> <span><code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm">npx skillsets install @namespace/name</code></span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-orange-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0">3.</span> <span>Files extract directly to your project. No .git folders, no bloat.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-orange-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0">4.</span> <span>Checksums verified against the registry automatically.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-ink mb-4 font-serif">Built with Valence</h2>
        <p>
          This site was built by <a href="https://github.com/supercollectible" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@supercollectible</a> using
          <a href="/skillset/@supercollectible/Valence" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Valence</a> — the first skillset in the registry.
          The infrastructure is MIT-licensed. Individual skillsets are licensed by their authors.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="pt-4 border-t border-border-ink">
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          Have a production-verified workflow? <a href="/contribute" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Contribute it</a>.
          Want to help review? <a href="https://github.com/skillsets-cc/main" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Become a co-maintainer</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
